699.overview:
Lornoxicam is an NSAID analgesic belonging to the oxicam class, used for mild to moderate acute and chronic pain and also acts as an anti-inflammatory and antipyretic. It is indicated for musculoskeletal pain, postoperative pain, inflammation in rheumatoid arthritis, osteoarthritis, acute lumbar-sciatic conditions, dysmenorrhea, and soft tissue inflammation.

MECHANISM OF ACTION

Lornoxicam is a potent inhibitor of cyclooxygenase enzymes (COX-1 and COX-2), which acts by reducing the synthesis of prostaglandins, substances that mediate pain, inflammation, and fever.

CONTRAINDICATIONS

Lornoxicam treatment is contraindicated in the following cases:

Patients with hypersensitivity to NSAIDs, including acetylsalicylic acid.
Acute heart failure.
History of gastrointestinal perforation or bleeding related to the use of NSAIDs.
Presence of active or previous gastrointestinal ulcers or bleeding.
Cerebrovascular hemorrhages or other types of active bleeding.
During the third trimester of pregnancy.
Patients with acute renal or hepatic failure.

SIDE EFFECTS

The most frequent adverse reactions are mild headache, dizziness, nausea, abdominal pain, dyspepsia, diarrhea, vomiting.

INTERACTIONS

Lornoxicam can interact with multiple medications, so it is recommended to inform your doctor of all the medications you are taking. Lornoxicam interacts with NSAIDs (such as acetylsalicylic acid and ibuprofen) and anticoagulant agents (such as warfarin) and antiplatelet agents (e.g., clopidogrel) and may lead to an increased risk of bleeding. NSAIDs decrease the therapeutic effect of antihypertensive drugs and should be used with caution in patients with underlying hypertension. It also interacts with corticosteroids, cimetidine, immunosuppressants, lithium, selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors (SSRIs), sulfonylureas, and some antibiotics, among other medications.

BRAND NAMES

